1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 3=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:01:28,310 --> 00:01:30,120
Why can't you keep your hands
to yourself?

4
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:32,040
We're about to leave.

5
00:01:32,040 --> 00:01:33,310
And you grabbed his goose.

6
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,070
What kind of person does that?

7
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:36,280
You don't know anything.

8
00:01:36,510 --> 00:01:37,350
Listen to me.

9
00:01:37,350 --> 00:01:38,430
Once we find the tunnel,

10
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,000
there might be

11
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,640
some toxic gas inside.

12
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:43,710
We've got this goose.

13
00:01:43,710 --> 00:01:44,680
Let's toss it in first.

14
00:01:44,950 --> 00:01:45,870
See if the path's safe.

15
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,680
Get up.

16
00:02:06,590 --> 00:02:08,030
You're tomb raiders?

17
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:11,360
Get up.

18
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,520
Then let's talk.

19
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,120
I can take you there,

20
00:02:16,030 --> 00:02:16,870
but...

21
00:02:17,190 --> 00:02:18,430
But I want fifty grand.

22
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:19,550
Sure thing.

23
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,520
You'd better keep your word.

24
00:02:22,630 --> 00:02:24,190
As long as you can lead us to the tomb.

25
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:25,640
Get up.

26
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:30,800
Go.

27
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:40,400
Boss, he slipped away again.

28
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,750
The energy of life animates this land.

29
00:02:56,150 --> 00:02:57,150
It flows within the earth

30
00:02:58,030 --> 00:03:00,240
and gathers here due to the terrain.

31
00:03:05,870 --> 00:03:06,750
Let's head in.

32
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:07,590
Don't move.

33
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:09,870
This web isn't naturally formed.

34
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:11,240
It's artificial.

35
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:12,080
Artificial?

36
00:03:12,430 --> 00:03:13,750
Something's off here.

37
00:03:14,310 --> 00:03:15,870
We'd better tread carefully.

38
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,360
So, how do we get in?

39
00:03:27,720 --> 00:03:28,560
Are you okay?

40
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,400
Are you okay, Chubby?

41
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,240
Lu,

42
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:35,800
what's wrong with you?

43
00:03:36,115 --> 00:03:37,549
Why can't you keep your hands still?

44
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:39,240
I was just trying to get in.

45
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,360
And you lit the fire?

46
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,200
Alright, enough.

47
00:03:42,190 --> 00:03:43,080
Let's get to work.

48
00:03:58,630 --> 00:04:00,240
Is this really necessary

49
00:04:01,190 --> 00:04:03,360
to keep people from noticing?

50
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,080
Wow.

51
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,870
You look like a bumpkin.

52
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:09,030
I'm telling you.

53
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:11,150
The more deserted the place,

54
00:04:11,470 --> 00:04:12,756
the better you've gotta build it.

55
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,470
This firewood isn't worth much.

56
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:22,240
Youxi, listen.

57
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,550
- Why...
- Lu.

58
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:30,360
Your athletic skills are terrible.

59
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,720
You tripped on a flat road?

60
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:32,560
This...

61
00:04:33,310 --> 00:04:34,720
This isn't flat at all.

62
00:04:35,630 --> 00:04:37,390
There's a dip here.

63
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:40,510
And a line right here.

64
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:42,870
Another one over there.

65
00:04:42,870 --> 00:04:43,720
Two lines.

66
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:44,606
They look like tracks.

67
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:45,910
Tracks?

68
00:04:47,630 --> 00:04:49,600
Is the tunnel below this statue?

69
00:04:50,830 --> 00:04:51,670
Let's give it a try.

70
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,200
Alright.

71
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:06,190
It won't budge.

72
00:05:10,390 --> 00:05:11,480
Push harder.

73
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,000
Use some strength.

74
00:05:13,756 --> 00:05:14,920
Why am I the only one trying?

75
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:15,770
Lend a hand.

76
00:05:15,780 --> 00:05:16,806
I don't even need to push.

77
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:19,160
A glance tells me

78
00:05:19,430 --> 00:05:20,270
there must be

79
00:05:20,430 --> 00:05:21,600
some kind of mechanism.

80
00:05:21,870 --> 00:05:23,230
Tell me. Where's that mechanism?

81
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,560
How would I know?

82
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:26,000
Then why talk so much?

83
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,680
It's just logical reasoning.

84
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:30,870
I'm just throwing ideas out.

85
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:35,000
Come here.

86
00:05:36,950 --> 00:05:38,120
There's a big gap here.

87
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,070
Don't you find that odd?

88
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,200
You're right.

89
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:42,840
I'll go check it out.

90
00:05:49,310 --> 00:05:50,870
So round and still acting smart.

91
00:06:11,310 --> 00:06:12,150
Lu,

92
00:06:12,630 --> 00:06:13,470
step back a bit.

93
00:06:16,070 --> 00:06:16,910
A little more back.

94
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,720
- Like this?
- There's a gap.

95
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:19,920
Ants are crawling out of it.

96
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:21,480
This stone base should be solid.

97
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:43,600
That's some fine craftsmanship.

98
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,430
They really went

99
00:06:46,430 --> 00:06:47,600
to great lengths for it.

100
00:06:55,390 --> 00:06:56,230
Someone's here.

101
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:57,510
Chubby, Lu.

102
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,080
Go down!

103
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:16,670
Shan!

104
00:07:19,390 --> 00:07:20,230
Hurry up.

105
00:07:20,270 --> 00:07:21,480
This tunnel slopes downward.

106
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:23,510
If nothing goes wrong,

107
00:07:23,916 --> 00:07:25,680
it should lead
straight to the ancient tomb.

108
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,560
Keep moving.

109
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,640
Look for a mechanism.

110
00:07:38,310 --> 00:07:41,510
Let's light those candles.

111
00:07:43,310 --> 00:07:44,150
Lu,

112
00:07:44,390 --> 00:07:45,430
you just started,

113
00:07:45,750 --> 00:07:46,789
and you're already scared?

114
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:48,600
No, not scared.

115
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:49,750
As you said earlier,

116
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:51,360
there might be toxic gas here.

117
00:07:51,830 --> 00:07:53,560
If we rush in like this,

118
00:07:53,950 --> 00:07:55,560
isn't that a bit careless?

119
00:07:56,950 --> 00:07:58,430
There's a big goose.

120
00:07:58,920 --> 00:07:59,953
Even if there's toxic gas,

121
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:02,270
it'll wilt first.

122
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:04,430
It's so close to us.

123
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,390
Even if it wilts,

124
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:06,830
can we get away with it?

125
00:08:07,870 --> 00:08:09,000
You never stop talking.

126
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:10,430
You just wanna light candles.

127
00:08:13,610 --> 00:08:14,480
See?

128
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,440
Relax.

129
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:25,950
Light another one.

130
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,120
The candle is gone.

131
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,360
It's gone.

132
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:50,270
The candle burned out.

133
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:56,600
The goose is gone too.

134
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,600
Huang Long, prep the blast.

135
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,640
Blow open the entrance.

136
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:02,550
Make sure Chen Youxi stays safe.

137
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:03,590
Got it.

138
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,000
This is spooky.

139
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:07,030
It feels creepy; let's head back.

140
00:09:07,270 --> 00:09:08,200
Don't continue.

141
00:09:08,270 --> 00:09:09,150
Going back?

142
00:09:09,150 --> 00:09:10,200
To get shot?

143
00:09:10,510 --> 00:09:12,870
The goose and the candle are gone.

144
00:09:12,870 --> 00:09:13,730
How to explain this?

145
00:09:13,740 --> 00:09:15,000
- Too spooky.
- Lu.

146
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:17,000
Maybe it's some trap we've never seen.

147
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:18,510
Don't be scared.

148
00:09:19,110 --> 00:09:20,310
Stop, wait a second.

149
00:09:20,510 --> 00:09:22,240
Guys, come on!

150
00:09:22,510 --> 00:09:23,480
Check this out.

151
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:25,030
See that?

152
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:27,000
I brought one of these. Want one?

153
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:27,840
This really works.

154
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:28,840
It'll hold them off.

155
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:29,720
Enough, Lu.

156
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,040
Listen to me.

157
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:32,120
Don't overthink it.

158
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:33,673
I've been with Chen for years.

159
00:09:34,270 --> 00:09:35,240
Just one thing to say.

160
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,910
Stick with Chen; you'll be fine.

161
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:38,120
Just relax.

162
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:38,960
You hear me?

163
00:09:40,390 --> 00:09:41,230
I'll go.

164
00:09:59,510 --> 00:10:00,390
The path ends here.

165
00:10:01,030 --> 00:10:01,870
What?

166
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,390
How's this a dead end?

167
00:10:06,150 --> 00:10:07,440
This tomb's way too small.

168
00:10:07,930 --> 00:10:09,440
We barely entered, and it's a dead end.

169
00:10:09,460 --> 00:10:10,320
Maybe we should

170
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:11,550
go back.

171
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,080
This place gives me the creeps.

172
00:10:13,910 --> 00:10:15,080
Didn't I just tell you?

173
00:10:15,150 --> 00:10:16,336
If we go back, we'll get shot.

174
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:18,200
No, maybe not necessarily.

175
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:19,480
We could try talking to them.

176
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,750
We could even work with them.

177
00:10:26,510 --> 00:10:27,350
Chubby,

178
00:10:27,510 --> 00:10:29,320
a wall just appeared here.

179
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,630
Didn't we just come through here?

180
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:36,590
How the heck...

181
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,480
What's going on here?

182
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:40,390
Where did this wall come from?

183
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:43,000
Where's the door?

184
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,040
This...

185
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:47,000
Why is there a wall?

186
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:49,840
Chen!

187
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:50,990
What's happening?

188
00:10:53,630 --> 00:10:55,750
Hey, don't bump into me!

189
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,150
It's coming this way!

190
00:10:58,480 --> 00:10:59,366
This one's moving too!

191
00:11:00,670 --> 00:11:02,320
Chubby, push harder!

192
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,790
I've never pushed this hard in my life!

193
00:11:15,510 --> 00:11:17,000
We're turning into hamburgers!

194
00:11:18,870 --> 00:11:20,440
What the heck is this?

195
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:36,030
I almost broke my neck!

196
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:39,360
Where the heck are we?

197
00:11:39,510 --> 00:11:41,480
The underworld?

198
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:44,870
Stop screaming!

199
00:11:52,550 --> 00:11:53,390
This...

200
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:56,360
Only a fool would follow you guys out!

201
00:11:59,630 --> 00:12:00,470
Chen.

202
00:12:00,870 --> 00:12:01,790
Look. What's this?

203
00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:04,600
This charm's in perfect shape.

204
00:12:04,870 --> 00:12:05,796
That's a real treasure.

205
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,670
He's a cripple.

206
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:11,030
You mean the one who built the temple?

207
00:12:14,030 --> 00:12:14,870
Lu.

208
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,440
Lu!

209
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:21,840
Chubby.

210
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:23,590
Get the door.

211
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:27,670
Put some muscle into it.

212
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:30,800
Reload complete.

213
00:12:43,550 --> 00:12:44,480
What's that sound?

214
00:13:30,550 --> 00:13:31,390
Come on.

215
00:13:33,390 --> 00:13:34,230
One, two.

216
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:41,790
Anyone here?

217
00:13:43,870 --> 00:13:45,480
Hey! Anybody!

218
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,870
Hey, you again!

219
00:14:00,030 --> 00:14:01,550
As I told you,

220
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:03,790
anyone who comes for the tomb

221
00:14:04,360 --> 00:14:05,840
deserves death.

222
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:08,840
That corpse must be the one
who built the temple.

223
00:14:09,670 --> 00:14:11,910
You trapped him here the same way,

224
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:13,870
leaving him to die.

225
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:15,960
Pretty clever of you.

226
00:14:17,790 --> 00:14:18,840
So, how does it feel?

227
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:21,600
So, the ghost stories about the temple,

228
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:23,960
the spider webs at the entrance,

229
00:14:24,020 --> 00:14:25,120
and the traps in the tunnel

230
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:26,030
were your doing.

231
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:27,910
Whose tomb are you guarding?

232
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:29,670
What lies in this chamber?

233
00:14:32,390 --> 00:14:33,320
Take care, everyone.

234
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,133
- Farewell.
- Get back here!

235
00:14:37,030 --> 00:14:37,870
Come back!

236
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,670
Fight me one-on-one!

237
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:41,470
Coward!

238
00:14:42,150 --> 00:14:43,000
Come back!

239
00:14:43,150 --> 00:14:45,270
Let us out of here!

240
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:52,680
It's over.

241
00:14:55,030 --> 00:14:56,790
We're doomed.

242
00:14:58,150 --> 00:15:00,360
I just came to watch the show.

243
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:01,750
Now, we're buried right here.

244
00:15:02,790 --> 00:15:04,390
How are we supposed to get out?

245
00:15:05,030 --> 00:15:06,630
Sorry, guys.

246
00:15:10,630 --> 00:15:11,960
What's there to be sorry for?

247
00:15:13,270 --> 00:15:14,110
In this life,

248
00:15:14,870 --> 00:15:17,910
I'd rather die together than live apart.

249
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:21,480
Having you guys here feels good.

250
00:15:31,670 --> 00:15:32,510
Alright.

251
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:36,000
In my life,

252
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:38,670
meeting you two

253
00:15:40,510 --> 00:15:41,350
is worth it.

254
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:47,480
Thanks.

255
00:15:52,670 --> 00:15:53,840
I can't catch my breath.

256
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,550
Lu, Lu!

257
00:15:55,790 --> 00:15:57,080
How are you holding up, Lu?

258
00:15:58,870 --> 00:15:59,910
I can't breathe.

259
00:16:00,390 --> 00:16:01,230
Lu!

260
00:16:02,270 --> 00:16:03,320
Hang in there!

261
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:05,800
Hang in there.

262
00:16:28,630 --> 00:16:30,080
Wait. I see light.

263
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,550
Who's that?

264
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:54,280
Report.

265
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,320
We found a stone gate outside.

266
00:17:08,750 --> 00:17:10,920
Five sets of footprints.
Deeper in front.

267
00:17:11,550 --> 00:17:12,880
They escaped from here.

268
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:14,640
Three sets should belong to those three.

269
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:15,819
Another pair is cloth shoes.

270
00:17:16,270 --> 00:17:18,110
It might be the farmer we fought with.

271
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:20,440
But there's also a size 37 pair.

272
00:17:20,790 --> 00:17:21,960
The stride's a bit smaller.

273
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:23,320
It's a woman.

274
00:17:37,440 --> 00:17:40,540
♪A tiny ark sails;
the sky opens its eyes♪

275
00:17:42,220 --> 00:17:45,900
♪Stillness in motion,
the earth plays its chord♪

276
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:51,540
♪A leaf falls;
we cross through time and space♪

277
00:17:51,690 --> 00:17:58,690
♪In a blink, all things rest
upon our hands♪

278
00:17:59,250 --> 00:18:10,270
♪La la♪

279
00:18:17,020 --> 00:18:19,010
♪No line divides the border♪

280
00:18:19,450 --> 00:18:21,790
♪Nothing limits your performance♪

281
00:18:21,790 --> 00:18:24,160
♪Everything shows perfect harmony♪

282
00:18:24,160 --> 00:18:26,850
♪Love circles the sky,
the earth, and our faith♪

283
00:18:28,350 --> 00:18:30,060
♪Hey hey hey♪

284
00:18:31,390 --> 00:18:33,210
♪Hey hey hey♪

285
00:18:35,860 --> 00:18:36,860
♪Hey hey♪

286
00:18:37,010 --> 00:18:38,010
♪Hey hey♪

287
00:18:39,470 --> 00:18:40,550
♪Hey hey♪

288
00:18:42,180 --> 00:18:46,380
♪Step into the galaxy of colors♪

289
00:18:46,970 --> 00:18:50,680
♪Stars connect our hearts as one♪

290
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:55,180
♪No difference between you and me♪

291
00:18:55,460 --> 00:18:57,790
♪No lead or side role on this stage♪

292
00:18:57,790 --> 00:19:00,000
♪A perfect life is something we share♪

293
